  "notes": "Sinhala (Sri Lanka). Typologically diverges from mainland IA: prenasalised stops /ᵐb ⁿd ⁿɖ ᵑɡ ⁿdʒ/ are phonemic (rare in IA); vowels /æ æː/ absent in most other IA languages; dental stops /t d/ distinct from retroflex /ʈ ɖ/ (no dental diacritic). Diglossia: formal (literary) vs. colloquial speech differ markedly.",
